claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Figure depicting the number needed to vaccinate per 100,000 adults aged ≥65 years to prevent influenza-related outcomes, comparing different flu vaccines (likely standard-dose, high-dose, and recombinant) The figure reports epidemiologic outcomes (numbers needed to vaccinate) rather than detailing hemagglutinin antigen content; it does not support the claim
